org/donate/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Candidates&#39; Guide</title> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Google Summer of Code (GSoC) Contributor Guide&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;This guide is intended for both prospective and accepted candidates of the GSoCprogram with Open Science L...&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://opensciencelabs.org/opportunities/gsoc/guides/contributor/?utm_source=documentation&amp;utm_medium=RSS&amp;utm_campaign=feed-syndication</link> <pubDate>Mon, 29 Jun 2026 01:10:18 +0200</pubDate><source url="https://opensciencelabs.org/feed_rss_created.xml">Open Science Labs</source><comments>https://opensciencelabs.org/opportunities/gsoc/guides/contributor/#__comments</comments><guid isPermaLink="true">https://opensciencelabs.org/opportunities/gsoc/guides/contributor/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Overview</title> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Open Science Labs Projects&lt;/h1&gt;&lt;p&gt;Open Science Labs (OSL) champions the intersection of open science andopen-source technology, fostering a vibrant community wh...&lt;/p&gt;</description><link>https://opensciencelabs.org/projects/?utm_source=documentation&amp;utm_medium=RSS&amp;utm_campaign=feed-syndication</link> <pubDate>Mon, 29 Jun 2026 01:10:18 +0200</pubDate><source url="https://opensciencelabs.org/feed_rss_created.xml">Open Science Labs</source><comments>https://opensciencelabs.org/projects/#__comments</comments><guid isPermaLink="true">https://opensciencelabs.org/projects/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Sponsorship</title> <author>OSL Team</author> <description>Support Open Science Labs and help sustain open science, open-source research software, mentorship, internships, community programs, and contributor pathways.</description><link>https://opensciencelabs.org/about/sponsorship/?utm_source=documentation&amp;utm_medium=RSS&amp;utm_campaign=feed-syndication</link> <pubDate>Wed, 17 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0200</pubDate><source url="https://opensciencelabs.org/feed_rss_created.xml">Open Science Labs</source><comments>https://opensciencelabs.org/about/sponsorship/#__comments</comments><guid isPermaLink="true">https://opensciencelabs.org/about/sponsorship/</guid> </item> <item> <title>ArxLang VS Code Extension: A Closer Look</title> <author>Yogendra Sankhla</author> <category>ArxLang</category> <category>Extension</category> <category>VS Code</category> <description>A closer look at the ArxLang VS Code extension, its features, and how it is built.</description><link>https://opensciencelabs.org/blog/arxlang-vs-code-extension-a-closer-look/?utm_source=documentation&amp;utm_medium=RSS&amp;utm_campaign=feed-syndication</link> <pubDate>Tue, 09 Jun 2026 09:30:00 +0200</pubDate><source url="https://opensciencelabs.org/feed_rss_created.xml">Open Science Labs</source><comments>https://opensciencelabs.org/blog/arxlang-vs-code-extension-a-closer-look/#__comments</comments><guid isPermaLink="true">https://opensciencelabs.org/blog/arxlang-vs-code-extension-a-closer-look/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Arx Project Update: A New Monorepo, Better Tooling, and the First Steps Toward a Bigger Ecosystem</title> <author>Ivan Ogasawara</author> <category>arx</category> <category>compiler</category> <category>llvm</category> <description>Arx is evolving into a broader language ecosystem for data-oriented computing. Recent updates include the new monorepo for ASTx, IRx, and Arx, early tooling like ArxPM, VS Code syntax highlighting, Douki docstring support, and an experimental Jupyter kernel. The language itself is also growing with features such as typed functions, classes, templates, collections, dataframes, and compiler/runtime improvements.</description><link>https://opensciencelabs.org/blog/arx-project-update-a-new-monorepo/?utm_source=documentation&amp;utm_medium=RSS&amp;utm_campaign=feed-syndication</link> <pubDate>Wed, 29 Apr 2026 09:30:00 +0200</pubDate><source url="https://opensciencelabs.org/feed_rss_created.xml">Open Science Labs</source><comments>https://opensciencelabs.org/blog/arx-project-update-a-new-monorepo/#__comments</comments><guid isPermaLink="true">https://opensciencelabs.org/blog/arx-project-update-a-new-monorepo/</guid> </item> <item> <title>OSL 2.0</title> <author>Ivan Ogasawara</author> <category>osl</category> <description>OSL 2.0 is a new chapter—and an open invitation. If you believe in Growth, Collaboration, and Impact, there&#39;s a place for you here: to learn in public, contribute to real projects, and grow into a leader who helps others do the same. Whether you&#39;re a student, a researcher, a maintainer, or simply someone who cares about open source and open science, we&#39;d love to meet you. Read our mission, join the conversation, and take your first step with us—one small contribution can become a life-changing journey.</description><link>https://opensciencelabs.org/blog/osl-2-0/?utm_source=documentation&amp;utm_medium=RSS&amp;utm_campaign=feed-syndication</link> <pubDate>Mon, 19 Jan 2026 09:30:00 +0100</pubDate><source url="https://opensciencelabs.org/feed_rss_created.xml">Open Science Labs</source><comments>https://opensciencelabs.org/blog/osl-2-0/#__comments</comments><guid isPermaLink="true">https://opensciencelabs.org/blog/osl-2-0/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Overview</title> <author>OSL Team</author> <description>Open Science Labs — empowered growth through belonging, mentorship, and purpose.</description><link>https://opensciencelabs.org/about/?utm_source=documentation&amp;utm_medium=RSS&amp;utm_campaign=feed-syndication</link> <pubDate>Mon, 19 Jan 2026 00:00:00 +0100</pubDate><source url="https://opensciencelabs.org/feed_rss_created.xml">Open Science Labs</source><comments>https://opensciencelabs.org/about/#__comments</comments><guid isPermaLink="true">https://opensciencelabs.org/about/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Three Years with Google Summer of Code: What I&#39;ve Learned</title> <author>Ivan Ogasawara</author> <category>gsoc</category> <category>mentoring</category> <category>open-source</category> <description>Three years in GSoC taught us one thing: mentoring matters more than code.As a 2025 mentoring org (with AlphaOneLabs, Extralit, Makim, Sugar), our playbook is simple—balance mentors, set explicit contribution rules, meet regularly; and for contributors: communicate publicly and ship small, tested PRs.</description><link>https://opensciencelabs.org/blog/three-years-with-google-summer-of-code-what-ive-learned/?utm_source=documentation&amp;utm_medium=RSS&amp;utm_campaign=feed-syndication</link> <pubDate>Sun, 02 Nov 2025 09:30:00 +0100</pubDate><source url="https://opensciencelabs.org/feed_rss_created.xml">Open Science Labs</source><comments>https://opensciencelabs.org/blog/three-years-with-google-summer-of-code-what-ive-learned/#__comments</comments><guid isPermaLink="true">https://opensciencelabs.org/blog/three-years-with-google-summer-of-code-what-ive-learned/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Packaging a VS Code Extension Using pnpm and VSCE</title> <author>Ansh Arora</author> <category>Automation</category> <category>Makim</category> <category>VSCode</category> <category>esbuild</category> <category>pnpm</category> <description>A step-by-step guide to packaging and publishing VS Code extensions with pnpm and vsce, covering how to avoid dependency resolution issues.</description><link>https://opensciencelabs.org/blog/packaging-a-vs-code-extension-using-pnpm-and-vsce/?utm_source=documentation&amp;utm_medium=RSS&amp;utm_campaign=feed-syndication</link> <pubDate>Sun, 31 Aug 2025 09:30:00 +0200</pubDate><source url="https://opensciencelabs.org/feed_rss_created.xml">Open Science Labs</source><comments>https://opensciencelabs.org/blog/packaging-a-vs-code-extension-using-pnpm-and-vsce/#__comments</comments><guid isPermaLink="true">https://opensciencelabs.org/blog/packaging-a-vs-code-extension-using-pnpm-and-vsce/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Language Server Protocol (LSP): How Editors Speak Code</title> <author>Ansh Arora</author> <category>Automation</category> <category>Developer Experience</category> <category>Makim</category> <description>The Language Server Protocol (LSP) powers modern code editors like VS Code by enabling real-time autocompletion, hover info, diagnostics, and more.</description><link>https://opensciencelabs.org/blog/language-server-protocol-lsp-how-editors-speak-code/?utm_source=documentation&amp;utm_medium=RSS&amp;utm_campaign=feed-syndication</link> <pubDate>Fri, 15 Aug 2025 09:30:00 +0200</pubDate><source url="https://opensciencelabs.org/feed_rss_created.xml">Open Science Labs</source><comments>https://opensciencelabs.org/blog/language-server-protocol-lsp-how-editors-speak-code/#__comments</comments><guid isPermaLink="true">https://opensciencelabs.org/blog/language-server-protocol-lsp-how-editors-speak-code/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Contribution Guidelines</title> <author>OSL Team</author> <description>Contribution Guidelines</description><link>https://opensciencelabs.org/opportunities/guides/contribution/?utm_source=documentation&amp;utm_medium=RSS&amp;utm_campaign=feed-syndication</link> <pubDate>Sun, 23 Mar 2025 00:00:00 +0100</pubDate><source url="https://opensciencelabs.org/feed_rss_created.xml">Open Science Labs</source><comments>https://opensciencelabs.org/opportunities/guides/contribution/#__comments</comments><guid isPermaLink="true">https://opensciencelabs.org/opportunities/guides/contribution/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Overview</title> <author>OSL Team</author> <description>Open Proposals</description><link>https://opensciencelabs.org/partnership/open-proposals/?utm_source=documentation&amp;utm_medium=RSS&amp;utm_campaign=feed-syndication</link> <pubDate>Sun, 23 Mar 2025 00:00:00 +0100</pubDate><source url="https://opensciencelabs.org/feed_rss_created.xml">Open Science Labs</source><comments>https://opensciencelabs.org/partnership/open-proposals/#__comments</comments><guid isPermaLink="true">https://opensciencelabs.org/partnership/open-proposals/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Community Training</title> <author>OSL Team</author> <description>Open Proposal: Community Training</description><link>https://opensciencelabs.org/partnership/open-proposals/community-training/?utm_source=documentation&amp;utm_medium=RSS&amp;utm_campaign=feed-syndication</link> <pubDate>Sun, 23 Mar 2025 00:00:00 +0100</pubDate><source url="https://opensciencelabs.org/feed_rss_created.xml">Open Science Labs</source><comments>https://opensciencelabs.org/partnership/open-proposals/community-training/#__comments</comments><guid isPermaLink="true">https://opensciencelabs.org/partnership/open-proposals/community-training/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Project Ideas</title> <author>OSL Team</author> <description>Open Source Software (OSS) Research Seed Project Ideas</description><link>https://opensciencelabs.org/opportunities/internships/oss-research-seed/project-ideas/?utm_source=documentation&amp;utm_medium=RSS&amp;utm_campaign=feed-syndication</link> <pubDate>Sun, 16 Mar 2025 00:00:00 +0100</pubDate><source url="https://opensciencelabs.org/feed_rss_created.xml">Open Science Labs</source><comments>https://opensciencelabs.org/opportunities/internships/oss-research-seed/project-ideas/#__comments</comments><guid isPermaLink="true">https://opensciencelabs.org/opportunities/internships/oss-research-seed/project-ideas/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Open Science Labs is participating in the Google Summer of Code 2025 as a Mentoring Organization!</title> <author>Open Science Labs Team</author> <category>google summer of code</category> <category>gsoc</category> <category>open-science</category> <category>open-source</category> <description>Open Science Labs (OSL) is participating as a mentoring organization in Google Summer of Code (GSoC) 2025 for the first time. Students and newcomers can join open-source projects, connect with mentors, and apply via the GSoC website. Visit the official page of OSL or Discord for details.</description><link>https://opensciencelabs.org/blog/open-science-labs-participating-google-summer-of-code-2025-mentoring-organization/?utm_source=documentation&amp;utm_medium=RSS&amp;utm_campaign=feed-syndication</link> <pubDate>Sat, 01 Mar 2025 09:30:00 +0100</pubDate><source url="https://opensciencelabs.org/feed_rss_created.xml">Open Science Labs</source><comments>https://opensciencelabs.org/blog/open-science-labs-participating-google-summer-of-code-2025-mentoring-organization/#__comments</comments><guid isPermaLink="true">https://opensciencelabs.org/blog/open-science-labs-participating-google-summer-of-code-2025-mentoring-organization/</guid> </item> </channel></rss>